  "prompt": "Does frosting expire or go bad?",
  "response": "Yes, frosting can expire and go bad. Here are some guidelines:\n\n1. Store-bought, unopened frosting:\n- Typically lasts 6-12 months past the printed date\n- Store in a cool, dry place\n- Check for signs of spoilage before use\n\n2. Homemade frosting:\n- Usually lasts 3-7 days in the refrigerator\n- Should be stored in an airtight container\n\n3. Signs of spoilage:\n- Mold growth\n- Off smell\n- Separation or strange texture\n- Discoloration\n\n4. Opened, store-bought frosting:\n- Refrigerate after opening\n- Generally good for 1-2 weeks\n- Always check the container's instructions\n\n5. Factors affecting shelf life:\n- Ingredients\n- Storage conditions\n- Exposure to air and moisture\n\nWhen in doubt, it's best to discard frosting if you're unsure about its freshness to avoid potential foodborne illness.",
